      "author": "yarhuoy (Ng Yar Huoy)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hi <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/matias.monday\">@Matias.Monday</a></p>\n<p>Thanks for your quick reply!</p>\n<p>Actually we want to implement in the Settings to our Custom Calendar App, the app feature is almost like the default Monday Calendar, this is our current custom setting (only support Person column):<br />\n</p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/2X/4/4c5a1eda75703382bc2de94a319e09da71fe72d9.png\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/2X/4/4c5a1eda75703382bc2de94a319e09da71fe72d9_2_690x381.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"690\" height=\"381\" /><div class=\"meta\">\n<span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1534×848 108 KB</span>\n</div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>I am wondering can we implement the exact same “Color by” settings by using the provided feature:</p><aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/2X/7/7bfd2edf3c0259b3048238de3e35866f88305b6b.png\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" />\n\n      <a href=\"https://developer.monday.com/apps/docs/quickstart-view\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">monday apps framework</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    \n\n<h3><a href=\"https://developer.monday.com/apps/docs/quickstart-view\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Quickstart Guide</a></h3>\n\n  <p>Step-by-step instructions to build a simple client-side monday app with React!</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>Or we will need to code every logic of every dropdownlist options by ourselves?</p>\n<p>Br, YarHuoy</p>"
